---
import Layout from '../layouts/BlogPost.astro';
import AboutHeroImage from '../assets/blog-placeholder-about.jpg';
---

<Layout
	title="About Me"
	description="Learn about the person behind 'A Book in the Hand' and my literary journey"
	pubDate={new Date('January 06 2025')}
	heroImage={AboutHeroImage}
>
	<p>
		Hello, and welcome to my little corner of the literary world! I'm the person behind <em>"A Book in the Hand,"</em> and I'm delighted you've found your way here.
	</p>

	<p>
		My love affair with books began in childhood, when I discovered that between the covers of a book, entire worlds were waiting to be explored. From fantasy epics to intimate memoirs, from classic literature to contemporary fiction, I've always believed that there's a perfect book for every mood, every moment, and every person.
	</p>

	<h2>Why I Started This Blog</h2>
	<p>
		As someone who reads voraciously (my goal is always to read at least one book per week), I found myself constantly recommending books to friends, family, and anyone who would listen. I realized I wanted to create a space where I could share these discoveries with fellow book lovers, and where we could build a community around our shared passion for great storytelling.
	</p>

	<p>
		The name "A Book in the Hand" plays on the old saying "a bird in the hand is worth two in the bush." To me, a good book in your hands is worth countless hours of entertainment, learning, and growth. There's something magical about holding a story that has the power to transport you, teach you, or completely change your perspective.
	</p>

	<h2>What You'll Find Here</h2>
	<p>
		This blog is primarily focused on book reviews, but you'll also find:
	</p>
	<ul>
		<li><strong>Honest book reviews</strong> – I believe in giving you the real scoop, both the good and the not-so-good</li>
		<li><strong>Reading lists and recommendations</strong> – Curated collections for different moods and interests</li>
		<li><strong>Literary discussions</strong> – Exploring themes, trends, and the art of storytelling</li>
		<li><strong>Author spotlights</strong> – Celebrating the writers who create these amazing worlds</li>
	</ul>

	<h2>My Reading Preferences</h2>
	<p>
		While I try to read across all genres, I have a particular soft spot for:
	</p>
	<ul>
		<li>Contemporary fiction with complex characters</li>
		<li>Historical fiction that brings the past to life</li>
		<li>Memoirs and biographies of fascinating people</li>
		<li>Literary fiction that makes me think</li>
		<li>Mysteries and thrillers that keep me guessing</li>
	</ul>

	<h2>Let's Connect</h2>
	<p>
		I believe the best part of reading is sharing the experience with others. If you've read something I've reviewed, I'd love to hear your thoughts! Did you love it as much as I did? Did we disagree completely? 
	</p>

	<p>
		Reading is deeply personal, and what moves one person might not resonate with another – and that's perfectly okay. My hope is that through these reviews, you'll discover your next favorite book, even if it's one I didn't personally connect with.
	</p>

	<p>
		Happy reading, and thank you for joining me on this literary journey!
	</p>
</Layout>
